,0.060922,0.049319]},{"section":10,"text":"I recall that in glaucoma, the cup-to-disc ratio increases, meaning the cup becomes deeper and larger.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037325,0.05489,0.074869,0.08904,0.10362,0.11022,0.11132,0.10871,0.10005,0.083886,0.067549,0.058515],"unified_progress":[0.036262,0.062098,0.083306,0.097068,0.1014,0.12319,0.10586,0.098199,0.091462,0.082335,0.066429,0.052395]},{"section":11,"text":"This is because the optic nerve fibers are being lost, so the cup (the area of the disc where the nerve fibers aren't present) gets bigger.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031669,0.049435,0.068348,0.082768,0.099543,0.10833,0.11166,0.11392,0.10773,0.09089,0.073588,0.062116],"unified_progress":[0.032564,0.058394,0.081059,0.096159,0.10226,0.11371,0.10856,0.10287,0.096338,0.087596,0.068664,0.051826]},{"section":12,"text":"The paracentral scotomas are also mentioned, which are blind spots or areas of the visual field loss that are more towards the center.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035021,0.057953,0.075098,0.089675,0.10073,0.1077,0.11052,0.10889,0.10015,0.08487,0.07143,0.057962],"unified_progress":[0.038681,0.066721,0.084477,0.096627,0.10289,0.10709,0.10367,0.099885,0.096265,0.084803,0.067418,0.051469]},{"section":13,"text":"That aligns with glaucoma, as the disease typically affects the paracentral regions first.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039364,0.051824,0.067537,0.079943,0.092923,0.1008,0.1054,0.10787,0.10438,0.093852,0.080965,0.075136],"unified_progress":[0.037537,0.058413,0.078281,0.090686,0.096052,0.1098,0.10337,0.10045,0.09541,0.089637,0.076395,0.063967]},{"section":14,"text":"Wait, but the patient's intraocular pressure is normal.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041906,0.07112,0.078796,0.084683,0.08865,0.09143,0.093869,0.093766,0.094868,0.095498,0.08966,0.075753]